// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apocky-PRIME-DIRECTIVE-v3
//
// § engine/render_forward.cssl  —  Forward+ rasterizer pipeline
//                                    (depth-prepass + 2D-tile-light-cull
//                                     + opaque-main + transparent + post-tonemap)
//
// CSSLv3 stage-0 engine module.
// Spec : specs/14_BACKEND.csl § HOST-SUBMIT BACKENDS (D3D12-priority Win)
//        specs/14_BACKEND.csl § OWNED DXIL EMITTER (stage-2 fleshing)
//        specs/14_BACKEND.csl § BACKEND-MATRIX (graphics row : Vulkan/D3D12/Metal)
//        specs/24_HOST_FFI.csl § ABI-STABLE-SYMBOLS § gpu (8 symbols)
//        specs/24_HOST_FFI.csl § CSSL-SIDE WRAPPERS § Gpu (effect-typed)
//        specs/24_HOST_FFI.csl § CAPABILITY-MATRIX § Cap<Gpu>
//        specs/24_HOST_FFI.csl § IFC-LABELS § Gpu-buffers (Public ;
//          output-image carries Sensitive<Frame> only on VR-headset)
//        specs/04_EFFECTS.csl § real-time-effect-tags (Deadline<>,
//          GpuSubmit, GpuInit, Realtime<Crit>)
//        specs/03_TYPES.csl § BASE-TYPES (vec2/vec3/vec4/mat4 builtin)
//        specs/12_CAPABILITIES.csl § THE SIX CAPABILITIES (Cap<Gpu> handle-tag)
//
// § ROLE
//   Forward+ multi-pass rasterizer driving the LoA in-game render path.
//   Targets 1440p (2560 × 1440) @ 144hz on the AMOLED-deep panel — the
//   Apocky canonical display. Frame-budget : 6_944 us (per
//   `stdlib/gpu::target_frame_us_144hz`). Mouse-to-photon ≤ 1 frame via
//   `LOA_FRAME_LATENCY = 1` (waitable swap-chain) + Mailbox-equivalent
//   present-mode + triple-buffer (`FRAMES_IN_FLIGHT_DEFAULT = 3`).
//
//   Pass-list (5 ; matches host-side `loa-host::fps_pipeline::PassKind`
//   subset for the forward-only stage-0 baseline) :
//     0 · DepthPrepass    — Z-only pass for early-Z + occlusion seed
//     1 · LightCull       — 16 × 16 tile compute · per-tile light-list
//     2 · OpaqueMain      — opaque draws against pre-built depth + light-list
//     3 · Transparent     — back-to-front alpha blend (post-opaque)
//     4 · PostTonemap     — Reinhard + sRGB OETF (HDR10 PQ-1000-nit when
//                            cfg.hdr=true)
//
// § PRIME_DIRECTIVE preserved
//   (a) NO surveillance — the renderer NEVER inspects framebuffer content for
//       biometric / behavioral inference. Frame contents are user-output only.
//   (b) Light-cull inputs (point / spot / dir lights) are SCENE data — they
//       carry the Public IFC label (per spec/24 § IFC-LABELS Gpu-buffers).
//       VR-headset body-pose path is DEFERRED (Cap<XR> separate slice).
//   (c) Cap<Gpu> witness consumed at every wrapper-fn entry — default-deny.
//   (d) Heap-alloc forbidden in per-frame record (Vec<VisibleMesh> /
//       Vec<Light> are pre-sized + grow-rare ; matches loa-host::fps_pipeline
//       INVARIANT 1).
//   (e) Deadline<6944us> tag on `forward_end_frame_present` — 144hz budget
//       is part of the FN signature (effect-row documentary at stage-0 ;
//       structural threading lands with MirEffectRow).
//   (f) ¬ blocking-acquire — `forward_begin_frame` takes `timeout_ns` ;
//       Err on miss · NO stall.
//
// § STAGE-0 NOTES
//   1. The 5 named passes lower to 5 host-FFI Pipeline handles (compiled via
//      `gpu::pipeline_compile` once at startup ; reused per-frame). Each
//      Pipeline carries its own DXIL/SPIRV blob — byte-IR is supplied by the
//      build pipeline (csslc emits the per-stage blob ; the blobs are
//      stitched into the fat-binary per spec/14 § FAT-BINARY ASSEMBLY).
//   2. Cmd-buf record / submit per-pass remain stage-1 stubs (per
//      stdlib/gpu::cmd_buf_record_stub + spec/24 § ABI-STABLE-SYMBOLS § gpu).
//      Stage-0 records DEFERRED ; this scaffold declares the surface +
//      orchestration so source-level engine code can already structure the
//      per-frame loop. The bodies become driver-active in stage-1 with NO
//      source-level rename.
//   3. Light-tile-cull tile-size = 16×16 pixels (256 threads-per-tile).
//      At 2560 × 1440 → 160 × 90 = 14_400 tiles. Per-tile MAX_LIGHTS = 256
//      (matches MAX_LIGHTS_DEFAULT). Total light-list buffer ≤ 14_400 × 256
//      × 4 = 14.7 MiB worst-case ; typical-scene < 1 MiB. Compares vs alt
//      8×8 (4× tile count, 64 threads/tile = under-utilize wave32/64 GPUs)
//      and 32×32 (poor light-list efficiency at edges). 16×16 = canonical
//      Forward+ choice (matches DOOM-2016 / Battlefield-V / Cyberpunk-2077).
//   4. MSAA opt-out at stage-0 (cfg.msaa = 1 default). TAA-future is the
//      modern AAA replacement (saves bandwidth ; better edge-quality on
//      foliage + thin-geometry). MSAA-4× / MSAA-8× paths are reserved by
//      `cfg.msaa : u32` for opt-in.
//   5. HDR10 PQ-1000-nit gated by `cfg.hdr=true` (per AMOLED-deep panel
//      discipline + spec/14 § HDR pathway). Tone-map pass branches on the
//      cached `surface_format_is_hdr` predicate — Reinhard for SDR ; PQ-OETF
//      passthrough for HDR10.
//   6. The fn-surface uses FREE-FUNCTIONS (no method-receivers) per spec/03
//      monomorph-only / no-trait-dispatch discipline. `&mut RenderResources`
//      carries the per-frame mutable state.
//   7. Import resolution : `use std::gpu::*` lands the gpu surface (Device,
//      Swapchain, Pipeline, ShaderIRKind, SurfaceFormat, Cap<Gpu> bits,
//      target_frame_us_144hz, etc.). `use std::window::*` lands Window +
//      TARGET_WIDTH_1440P / TARGET_HEIGHT_1440P. `use std::time::*` lands
//      time_monotonic_ns + frame_budget_ns_for_hz. The cross-engine imports
//      (`com.apocky.engine.scene::*` + `com.apocky.engine.ecs::*`) are
//      spec-contract'd but the modules are running in parallel — at stage-0
//      monomorph these resolve once all engine modules co-compile in the
//      same fat-binary.
//      // N! syntax-uncertain : `use std::gpu::*` glob-import vs. selective
//      //    `use std::gpu::{Device, Swapchain, ...}`. Existing stdlib uses
//      //    selective-import ; the glob form is per spec/03 module-system
//      //    rules. We use the SELECTIVE form below (safer ; matches
//      //    examples/hello_triangle.cssl precedent).
//
// § INVARIANTS
//   - `ForwardConfig.tile_size` ∈ {8, 16, 32} (16 = default) ; other values
//     reject via InvalidInput.
//   - `ForwardConfig.max_lights` ≤ 1024 (hardware-binding-limit on D3D12
//     ROOT_DESCRIPTOR_TABLE size ; 256 = default).
//   - `ForwardConfig.msaa` ∈ {1, 2, 4, 8} (1 = default, no-MSAA).
//   - `ForwardFrame.swapchain_image_idx` ∈ [0, FRAMES_IN_FLIGHT_DEFAULT).
//   - Pipeline handles in `ForwardPipelines` ≠ 0 after successful compile ;
//     0 = uninitialized sentinel.
//   - Per-frame `forward_pass_*` fns DO NOT allocate (Vec<VisibleMesh> /
//     Vec<Light> are pre-sized inputs ; grow happens out-of-band).
//   - `forward_end_frame_present` carries Deadline<6944us> at 144hz target.

